To know the GIT version 
$git --version


To initialize GIT repository
$git init


To get the status of the folder
$git status


To display list of added users
$git config --global --list


To add users
$git config --global user.email 'rajkarde@gmail.com'
$git config --global user.name 'rajkarde'


To add file to the staging area
$git add git.txt


To commit
$git commit -m 'first commit by Raj'
(the file will now enter the repository)


To show log of every file created
$git log
$git log --oneline
$git log --oneline git.txt
$git log --oneline <you can also add the ID here>


Pull 
Step 1: $git remote add origin <link of the code in GitHub>
Step 2: $git remote show origin
Step 3: $git pull origin main (main is the branch, you can add any targeted branch)


Push
Step 1: $ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4034 -C "rajkarde@gmail.com"
Step 2: Git Hub stuff......
Step 3: $git add raj
Step 4: $git add raj.pub
Step 5: $git status
Step 6: $git push -u origin master
